This documentation is only for a quick start.
The reference documentation is in DOCUMENTATION/Welcome.xml

To check if TOMUSS works, run the regression tests:

	make regtest1

==============================================================================
                       To try TOMUSS with modifying anything
==============================================================================

Launch TOMUSS without authentication:

    make translations
    ./tomuss.py regtest                 # displays many messages the first time

URL to use to connect to the server:

    http://127.0.0.1:8888/=super.user
    http://127.0.0.1:8888/=ue1.master

To create ou edit a table:

    http://127.0.0.1:8888/=ue1.master/2010/Printemps/UE-INF1001L
    http://127.0.0.1:8888/=ue1.master/2009/Dossiers/tablename      (private)
    http://127.0.0.1:8888/=ue1.master/2009/Public/tablename        (public)

To launch a 'suivi' server:
    ./suivi.py 2012 Printemps 8890 regtest
The parameters MUST be the ones defined in LOCAL/config.py

To configure TOMUSS:

    http://127.0.0.1:8888/=super.user/0/Dossiers/config_table

==============================================================================
                     Using TOMUSS in production
==============================================================================

Look at 'configuration.py' configuration file. DO NOT MODIFY IT.
change the values in your LOCAL files:

	LOCAL/config.py


To start/stop all the servers :
	- 'make' to start them all.
	- 'make stop' to stop them.


==============================================================================
                     To change the TOMUSS version
==============================================================================

Follow this procedure:
	* Retrieve new sources.
	* Put your modifications in LOCAL
	* 'make stop' in the old version
	* 'make start' in the new version

It is a good idea to make an install script (see SCRIPTS/install)


